(1) A person commits an offence if that person— (a) willfully delays or obstructs an inspector in the performance of the inspector ’s functions under this Act; (b) refuses to give an inspector reasonable assistance as the inspector may require for the purposes of performing the inspector ’s functions; (c) impersonates an inspector or presents oneself to be an inspector ; or (d) knowingly or negligently gives an inspector false or misleading information orally, in writing or otherwise.
